@NODE   system
@TITLE  "Cookie / System requirements"

Cookie should run on any Amiga system with OS 2.04 or higher,
one disk drive and 512kb memory.

If there is any trouble running Cookie on your machine,
please send @{"me" LINK contact} a bug report, thank you !
@ENDNODE

@NODE   add
@TITLE  "Cookie / Add"

By pressing the "Add" button (keyboard abbreviation: a) you
adds an empty cookie to the actual cookie list.

The pre-defined text for a cookie such this is: "No cookie.".

Change the text by entering a new cookie in the text fields.
@ENDNODE

@NODE   del
@TITLE  "Cookie / Del"

The "Del" button (keyboard abbreviation: d) deletes the actual
cookie from the actual cookie list.

It is not possible to get the cookie back after deleting !
@ENDNODE

@NODE   firstlast
@TITLE  "Cookie / First, Last"

By pressing the "First" button (keyboard abbreviation: f) or
the "Last" button (keyboard abbreviation: l),Cookie jumps to
the start or end of the actual cookie list.
@ENDNODE

@NODE   prevnext
@TITLE  "Cookie / Prev, Next"

By pressing the "Prev" button (keyboard abbreviation: p)
or the "Next" button (keyboard abbreviation: n),  Cookie
goes one cookie back or further.
@ENDNODE

@NODE   flush
@TITLE  "Cookie / Flush"

By pressing the "Flush" button (keyboard abbreviation: u)
all cookies will be deleted from the actual list.

Make sure you really want to flush all cookies !
It is not possible to get them back !
@ENDNODE

@NODE   load
@TITLE  "Cookie / Load"

With the "Load" button (keyboard abbreviation: o) you can
load any cookie databases. Please remember that the data-
base will be appended to the actual list.

So it is recommented to flush all cookies from the actual
list before loading a new database.
@ENDNODE

@NODE   save
@TITLE  "Cookie / Save"

With the "Save" button (keyboard abbreviation: s) you can
save the actual database to any file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE   print
@TITLE  "Cookie / Print"

With the "Print" button (keyboard abbreviation: r) you can
print the actual database.
@ENDNODE

@NODE   about
@TITLE  "Cookie / About"

By pressing the "About" button (keyboard abbreviation: b) you
get some informations about the program and the author.
@ENDNODE

@NODE   quit
@TITLE  "Cookie / Quit"

With the "Quit" button (keyboard abbreviation: q) you
quit Cookie. Remember that all cookies in the actual
database will be lost !
@ENDNODE

@NODE   format
@TITLE  "Cookie / Format"

A cookie data file has the following format:

    <cookie>
    <empty line>
    <cookie>
    <empty line>
    <...>

A cookie can have max. 3 lines. It is not possible to do
anything like this:

        This is a line...

        And another line...

if you want to let them one cookie!
This example would cause two cookies!

I hope these are not so much format restrictions.
@ENDNODE

